  "tables": [
    {
      "block_id": "23c4750c-f3ba-800c-bfe6-f531fb159055",
      "heading": "Summary Table REC",
      "rows": [
        [
          "Context",
          "Teaching Method",
          "Recommender System Type",
          "Target of Recommendation",
          "Students",
          "Courses",
          "Data sources",
          "Initialization Method",
          "Updates to Recommendations",
          "Preprocessing Details",
          "Recommendation types",
          "Evaluation",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Higher Education",
          "E-Learning",
          "Hybrid",
          "Suggest functional and motivational materials",
          "OULAD (among other Datasets)",
          "Not Applicable",
          "LMS logs,\n",
          "– MOSD: initialize non‑rated items to 0, denoise repeated trials– EC/DBSCAN: initial ε, minPts chosen randomly– MASO: tune ε & minPts via anarchic society optimization– EGSP: seed candidate sequences from denoised data\n– ETSVM: initial hyperplane via Lagrange multipliers",
          "Requires retraining to obtain new recommendations per learner:\n\n1. MOSD cleans logs\n2. EC clusters users\n3. MASO tunes clustering\n4. EGSP mines seq. patterns\n5. ETSVM trains and predicts\n6. Trust‑weighted mean ranks items",
          "Modified One Source Denoising is used: this is meant to eliminate “steps” that are in disagreement with the general behavior of the users →> remove the “noise”.\n\nDBSCAN is used to cluster users, which will later.\n\nEGSP stage‑wise candidate gen, pruning, hash‑tree search to be used for Support Vector Reggression\n\n",
          "Top-N recommended items",
          "MAE (5–19.2%)\nAccuracy (82–98%)\nRanking Score\nRecall\nPrecision\nQuery processing time (ms/sec)",
          "Authors propose an improvement to an Hybrid DBSCAN into SVM recommender system via the addition of steps specifically meant to reduce noise.\n\n \n\nOutperforms CF, MDHS, UPOD, HR, TBHR, MCIF, SPFR, CIHR, DSHR on all major metrics across 16 datasets. OULAD is one of the used datasets.",
          "– Expert‑set initial ratings (MOSD) may bias results\n– Offline static evaluation (no live deployment)\n– Many hyperparameters tuned on simulated logs\n– Assumes sufficient repeated trials per user\n– No user‑study or real‑time adaptation beyond batch runs"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
  ],
